            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "It looks like there was a problem with the plot. Let's proceed by finding the roots numerically for the equation \\(\\sin(x) + x^2 = 42\\).\n\nWe'll use a root-finding algorithm (such as Newton's method) to estimate the solutions near the region where \\(x^2\\) is close to 42, i.e., \\(x \\approx \\pm \\sqrt{42}\\).\n\nLet me compute the value.",
